 organizations to tackle transnational drug trafficking. They participate in regional and global initiatives to share intelligence and best practices in drug control.\n\nIt's important to note that Singapore has some of the world's strictest drug laws, including the mandatory death penalty for trafficking certain quantities of drugs. These stringent measures reflect the government's commitment to maintaining a drug-free society.\n\nIf you or someone you know is struggling with drug addiction, there are resources available for help. You can contact the Singapore Anti-Narcotics Association (SANA) at 1800-555-0555 or visit their website for more information on addiction recovery programs and support services."
