rotection:**\n   - Many digital payment platforms offer consumer protection features, such as transaction alerts, account lockouts, and reimbursement policies in case of unauthorized transactions. These measures help mitigate the impact of cybercrime on individuals.\n\n### What You Can Do:\n\n- **Stay Informed:** Regularly check updates from your bank and other financial service providers regarding new security measures and potential threats.\n- **Be Cautious:** Never share your login credentials or OTPs with anyone, and be wary of unsolicited emails or messages asking for personal information.\n- **Use Secure Networks:** Avoid using public Wi-Fi for financial transactions, as they can be less secure.\n- **Report Suspicious Activity:** If you notice anything unusual, report it to SingCERT or your financial institution immediately.\n\nOverall, while the rise of digital payments has brought convenience and efficiency, it has also created new challenges in terms of cybersecurity. However, with the right precautions and a supportive regulatory environment, Singapore remains a safe place to conduct digital transactions."
