perates a 24-hour hotline where individuals can seek help anonymously. Additionally, there are several rehabilitation centers and support groups like the Singapore Anti-Narcotics Association (SANA) and the Singapore After-Care Association (SACA) that offer ongoing support.\n\n7. **Community Watch and Reporting**: Neighbors and community members are encouraged to report any suspicious activities related to drug abuse. This creates a vigilant community that helps authorities intervene early and effectively.\n\n8. **Reintegration Programs**: For youth who have completed their rehabilitation, there are reintegration programs to help them return to society and avoid relapse. These programs include job placement assistance and continuous counseling.\n\nIf you or someone you know is struggling with drug addiction, please reach out to the CNB helpline at 1800-355-8500 or visit their website for more information on how to get help. Remember, it's better to seek help early and avoid the serious consequences of drug abuse."
