terrorism.\n   - The **International Centre for Political Violence and Terrorism Research (ICPVTR)** at the S. Rajaratnam School of International Studies (RSIS) plays a significant role in conducting research and offering training to both local and international participants.\n\n6. **Financial Measures:**\n   - Singapore collaborates with international financial institutions and regulatory bodies to combat the financing of terrorism.\n   - This includes participation in the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) and the implementation of FATF standards to prevent money laundering and terrorist financing.\n\n7. **Legal Framework:**\n   - The **Internal Security Act (ISA)** allows for the detention of individuals without trial if they pose a significant threat to national security, including terrorism.\n   - Singapore works with other countries to ensure that legal frameworks are aligned and effective in dealing with cross-border terrorism.\n\nThrough these collaborative efforts, Singapore aims to stay ahead of emerging threats and maintain a robust defense against terrorism."
